<section id="about">
    <h1>What is this?</h1>

    <p>
        This application is a tool to help us &mdash; the community &mdash; record, improve and select
        the actual presentations for <a href="<%= Settings.main_site %>"><%= Settings.event_name %></a>.
        The code is based on <a href="http://rubymanor.org/">Ruby Manor's</a> original
        <a href="http://vestibule.rubymanor.org/proposals">vestibule app</a>, and we are really thankful for that!
        With this tool we will be able to have our conference the way we want it - at least as far as the presentations go :-)
    </p>

    <p>
        <strong><%= Settings.event_name %> would be a lesser conference without your presentations</strong>.
        We think that almost everyone has something interesting to say,
        so please think about that fun or unusual or difficult or surprising thing
        you&rsquo;ve done recently and submit a talk (or several!) so that everyone can hear about it.
    </p>

    <p>
        We welcome all kinds of engaging Ruby related presentations,
        however we will be even happier if you propose an original presentation which
        will not appear in any other conference prior to <%= Settings.event_name %>.
        Ruby was first coded in 1993 and so this summer we'd like to celebrate its 20th birthday
        by having the plethora of presentations focused mostly on the language,
        its evolution, its future and its internals wherever possible.
    </p>
</section>

